<topic id="wsdl-validation">
  <title>Validating WSDL Documents</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>WSDL documents<indexterm>Validation</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>By default, WSDL files are validated as you type. To change this, <ph
        conkeyref="reusables-preferences-pages/open-the-preferences-page"/>, go to <menucascade>
        <uicontrol>Editor</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol>Document Checking</uicontrol>
      </menucascade>, and deselect the <xref
        href="preferences-editor-document-checking.dita#preferences-editor-document-checking/enable-auto-validation"
          ><uicontrol>Enable automatic validation</uicontrol> option</xref>. </p>
    <p>To validate a WSDL document manually, select the <uicontrol><image
          href="../img/Validate16.png" id="image_w5p_bsv_sr"/> Validate</uicontrol> action from the
          <uicontrol><image href="../img/ValidateDrop.png" id="image_sfz_bsv_sr"/>
        Validation</uicontrol> toolbar drop-down menu or the <menucascade product="developer editor">
        <uicontrol>Document</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol>Validate</uicontrol>
      </menucascade><uicontrol product="developerEclipse editorEclipse">XML</uicontrol> menu. The
      validation problems are highlighted directly in the editor, making it easy to locate and fix
      any issues.</p>
  </body>
</topic>
